\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Preheat the oven to 200 degrees F.\
Heat a cast-iron skillet or griddle over medium-high heat. When hot add the oil, onions and bell peppers, and cook, stirring, until caramelized, about 6 minutes. Add the garlic, salt, and pepper, and cook, stirring, for 30 seconds. Push off to 1 side of the griddle.\
Add the meat to the hot pan and cook, stirring and breaking up the meat, until almost no longer pink, about 2 minutes. Mix in the sauteed vegetables. Top with cheese slices and \cf2 melt\cf0 . Spoon the cheesy meat mixture into the warm buns and serve immediately with condiments of choice. \
